Package: fastclogit
Type: Package
Title: Fast Conditional Logit for Large-Scale Choice Data
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("Jesper", "Lindmarker", email = "jesper.lindmarker@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Memory-efficient conditional logit estimation using Rcpp, designed
    for large-scale discrete choice models with millions to hundreds of millions
    of rows. Features include a formula interface with automatic factor
    expansion, McFadden/Manski sampling correction offsets, clustered sandwich
    standard errors, collinearity detection, and KHB mediation decomposition
    (Kohler, Karlson & Holm, 2011). The Newton-Raphson optimizer uses three-tier
    convergence (gradient norm, relative log-likelihood, stall detection) for
    robust convergence on very large datasets. Avoids the model.frame/model.matrix
    memory duplication that makes survival::clogit() infeasible on large datasets.
URL: https://github.com/jeppelina/fastclogit
BugReports: https://github.com/jeppelina/fastclogit/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.0), stats
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
